    "body": "@jorisvandenbossche so the issue was that when installed, if ``conftest.py`` is at the top-level (and not below pandas), then its not installed; this can be resolved by by actually including it as a data file in ``setup.py``, but then need to have to explicity tell ``pytest`` . This *only* matters for ``pandas.test()``; so we *could* explicity path it in there.\r\n\r\nBut this is just simpler. In any even I made the ``BUILD_TEST`` build now run ``pandas.test()`` so this is tested anyhow."
